# bike-radar-docs sample: 3204 V2 target frames during an overtake
# window: 2 minutes centred on a rear-overtake event
# contents: ~1150 V2 target frames on char 3204, interleaved with battery
#   reads on 2a19 and a handful of 2811 status notifications.
#
# This is the *payload* portion of a RearVue 820 session - the unlock
# handshake has already happened. Feed each `3204` line through
# decode_3204.py (python) or RadarV2Decoder.kt (kotlin).
#
# Format (same as the rest of samples/):
#   <ms_since_start> <char_tail_4hex> <hex_bytes_no_spaces>
# Timestamps are normalised so the first data line is 0 ms (see
# tools/normalize_sample.py); inter-frame deltas are preserved exactly.
#
# Notable events in this window (times are `ms_since_start`):
#   ~t=54 s: cluster of vehicle tracks appear behind the bike
#   ~t=86 s: tid=96 enters reporting range at zone=1 (real ~31.7m),
#            crosses the 25.6m boundary (b2 wraps to high values, zone
#            rotates to 0), then approaches smoothly to ~12m before
#            receding.
#   ~t=93 s: tid=103 next overtake, shorter track.
#
# The 25.6m zone boundary is a great exercise for a decoder under test -
# naive implementations that treat byte[2] as a standalone uint8 * 0.1m
# see these as phantom 25m jumps and typically quarantine the track.
